verbose_text: The results showed a dramatic increase at lambda = 610 nm in the fluorescence emission spectrum when the amount of DSN enzyme was increased from 0.01 U to 0.5 U. XREF_FIG, in which F 0 and F were the NMM fluorescence intensity at lambda = 610 nm in the absence and presence of miR-141 respectively presented the fluorescence ratio value (F/F 0 -1) affected by the amount of DSN enzyme.
